             was indicted for <rs id="t18300916-343-off1761" type="offenceDescription">
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-off1761" type="offenceCategory" value="theft"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-off1761" type="offenceSubcategory" value="simpleLarceny"></interp>
               stealing, on the <rs id="t18300916-343-cd1762" type="crimeDate">28th of July</rs>
                     <join result="offenceCrimeDate" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-343-off1761 t18300916-343-cd1762"></join>, 2 gowns, value 5s.; 2 aprens, value 2s.; 1 shift, value 1s.; 9 caps, value 5s.; 3 towels, value 2s.; 2 napkins, value 1s.; 3 petticoats, value 2s.; 3 night-gowns, value 2s.; 1 hair-brush, value 6d.; 4 combs, value 2s., and 2 tooth-brushes, value 6d.
            </rs>, the goods of 
               
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-victim2789" type="victimName">
                     Mary 
                     Bland
                  <interp inst="t18300916-343-victim2789" type="surname" value="Bland"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-victim2789" type="given" value="Mary"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-victim2789" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                     <join result="offenceVictim" targOrder="Y" targets="t18300916-343-off1761 t18300916-343-victim2789"></join>
                  </persName>
               
            .</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-person2790">
                  MARY 
                  BLAND
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2790" type="surname" value="BLAND"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2790" type="given" value="MARY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2790" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I left my trunk, containing the articles stated, at Mr. McGowan's, on the 27th of July, when I went to Marylebone workhouse to be confined - when I got out I went for my box, and the landlady told me the prisoner had been and taken my box and her own; I had never allowed her to take the box or the articles; she had left there- I never heard of her till within three weeks, when she was in the workhouse; I went there with an officer - I found her with my cap on her head.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined by MR. HEATON. Q. Have you any other name but Mary? A. My name is Mary Ann, but I always went by the name of Mary; I have never been called Mary Ann since I was a child.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-person2791">
                  ISABELLA 
                  BURGOYNE
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2791" type="surname" value="BURGOYNE"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2791" type="given" value="ISABELLA"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2791" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prosecutrix left a trunk at my house, it was locked; the prisoner came, said she came for her own box and for Mary's, and asked what there was to pay - I said nothing at all, and asked what she was going to do with Mary's; she said, to take it to the workhouse - I only knew the prosecutrix by the name of Mary.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-person2792">
                  ANN 
                  FOY
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2792" type="surname" value="FOY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2792" type="given" value="ANN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2792" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . The prisoner became a lodger where I was- I pawned two or three articles by her orders.</p>
               <p>Cross-examined. Q. Where did you receive the articles from her? A. At a house where I worked; I did not assist in opening the box - I was on the opposite side of the kitchen when it was opened; the prisoner said Mary had got the key in a mistake, and she must have it opened, as she wanted something.</p>
               <p>COURT. Q. Did Mary Bland authorize you to take any of the things? A. No.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-person2793">
                  HENRY 
                  HAYES
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2793" type="surname" value="HAYES"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2793" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2793" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am a shopman to Mr. Baylis, a pawnbroker. 
               <persName id="t18300916-343-person2794">
                  Ann 
                  Foy
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2794" type="surname" value="Foy"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2794" type="given" value="Ann"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2794" type="gender" value="female"></interp>
                  </persName>
             pawned a petticoat for 1s., a gown for 2s., and some other things with me.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t18300916-343-person2795">
                  JOHN 
                  ANDREWS
               <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2795" type="surname" value="ANDREWS"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2795" type="given" value="JOHN"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t18300916-343-person2795" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
            . I am an officer. I took the prisoner, and produce these articles, which the prosecutrix identified- I took this cap off the prisoner's head.</p>
               <p>MARY BLAND. These are all mine.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence. I did not break the box.</p>
